    "author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
    "body": "Hello @dattasid, and thank you for your concern about security.\r\n\r\nWe agree that setting up approvals would have a huge cost for the attacker. But you are also saying that by doing so, the attacker would \"making gas costs for operations on this NFT very high\". This last part I don't quite understand. \r\n\r\nHow would this attack be detrimental to anyone but the attacker himself?\r\n\r\nAlso, please keep in mind that this is an implementation of [a standard](https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-721). So maybe this issue reaches beyond our implementation.",
