    "body": "I am new to Ethereum, just trying to understand, thanks!\r\n\r\nAfter I filed this, I did more research and seems like existing size of a `mapping` does not add gas to future operations on it. This was non intuitive, so I guess I over reacted. \r\n\r\nIf you do not see any impact of an attacker being able to balloon the size of  a `mapping` in a NFT, Please close this issue. I suppose Ethereum was designed to be resistant to this.\r\n",
